{"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/matchinforef\/ispartialmatch"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"title":"isPartialMatch","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"symbolKind":"property","extendedModule":"GLib","roleHeading":"Instance Property","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"isPartialMatch","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib17MatchInfoProtocolPAAE09isPartialB0Sbvp::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib12MatchInfoRefV","role":"symbol"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MatchInfoRef","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MatchInfoRef\/MatchInfoProtocol-Implementations"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"isPartialMatch","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"kind":"text","text":" { "},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Consider, for example, an application where a human is required to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"type in data for a field with specific formatting requirements. An","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"example might be a date in the form ddmmmyy, defined by the pattern"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"^\\d?\\d(jan|feb|mar|apr|may|jun|jul|aug|sep|oct|nov|dec)"},{"type":"text","text":"\\d\\d$”."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If the application sees the user’s keystrokes one by one, and can","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"check that what has been typed so far is potentially valid, it is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"able to raise an error as soon as a mistake is made.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"GRegex supports the concept of partial matching by means of the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"partialSoft","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"partialHard"},{"text":" flags.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"When they are used, the return code for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_regex_match()"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_regex_match_full()"},{"type":"text","text":" is, as usual, "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for a complete match, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"text":" otherwise. But, when these functions","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":", you can check if the match was partial calling"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_match_info_is_partial_match()"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The difference between ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"partialSoft"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"partialHard","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is that when a partial match is encountered"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"with "},{"code":"partialSoft","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", matching continues to search for a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"possible complete match, while with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"partialHard"},{"text":" matching","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"stops at the partial match."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"When both "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"partialSoft"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"partialHard","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"are set, the latter takes precedence."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"There were formerly some restrictions on the pattern for partial matching.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The restrictions no longer apply.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"See ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pcrepartial(3)"},{"text":" for more information on partial matching.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MatchInfoRef\/isPartialMatch"},"abstract":[{"text":"Usually if the string passed to g_regex_match*() matches as far as","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it goes, but is too short to match the entire pattern, "},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"returned. There are circumstances where it might be helpful to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"distinguish this case from other cases in which there is no match.","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MatchInfoRef":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"MatchInfoRef","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","title":"MatchInfoRef","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/matchinforef","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A GMatchInfo is an opaque struct used to return information about"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"matches.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MatchInfoRef","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MatchInfoRef"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib","kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","role":"collection"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MatchInfoRef/MatchInfoProtocol-Implementations":{"title":"MatchInfoProtocol Implementations","abstract":[],"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MatchInfoRef\/MatchInfoProtocol-Implementations","role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/matchinforef\/matchinfoprotocol-implementations","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MatchInfoRef/isPartialMatch":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"isPartialMatch","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/matchinforef\/ispartialmatch","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MatchInfoRef\/isPartialMatch","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"isPartialMatch"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Usually if the string passed to g_regex_match*() matches as far as","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"it goes, but is too short to match the entire pattern, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"text":" is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"returned. There are circumstances where it might be helpful to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"distinguish this case from other cases in which there is no match.","type":"text"}]}}}